      "description": "By the time At the Gates reconvened to write and record At War with Reality, Adrian Erlandsson had spent the better part of two decades building a professional touring and recording career away from the band — with The Haunted (which he co-founded in 1996), Cradle of Filth (1999–2006), and Paradise Lost (2009–2016). The kit he brought to those 2014 Studio Fredman sessions reflects that development: a Tama Starclassic Bubinga in a transparent black finish, the same rig documented from his Paradise Lost years and carried forward, essentially unchanged, into every At the Gates and Haunted recording since.\n\nThe four-tom, double-bass configuration — twin 22\" x 18\" kick drums, 10\" and 12\" rack toms, 16\" and 18\" floor toms — mirrors the double-kick approach he used on Slaughter of the Soul, but on dramatically more capable hardware. Bubinga is a dense African hardwood that Tama has used since the 1990s for its Starclassic series specifically because of its low-end focus and strong projection, qualities suited to a drummer who needs his kick drums to cut cleanly through layered, tremolo-picked guitar tracks.\n\nWhere the Slaughter of the Soul kit was studio house gear chosen out of necessity, the Starclassic Bubinga is a rig Erlandsson selected and refined across years of touring — the difference between a budget death metal band's constraints in 1994 and an established professional's considered setup twenty years later.",
