      "shell": "Bubinga hardwood",
      "description": "Erlandsson's snare for At War with Reality was the matching Bubinga-shell snare from his Starclassic setup — a 14\" x 6.5\" drum considerably deeper and more resonant than the studio snare used on Slaughter of the Soul nearly twenty years earlier. Where the 1995 sessions produced a dry, tight crack through minimal-ambience close-miking, the At War with Reality snare carries more body and depth, in keeping with Jens Bogren's fuller, more contemporary mix.\n\nThe Bubinga shell's dense, hardwood construction produces a full-bodied crack with strong low-mid presence, giving the snare enough weight to sit prominently against Studio Fredman's still-direct recording approach while retaining the articulation needed for the album's blast-beat passages. Fredrik Nordström's engineering kept the drum sound honest and largely unprocessed at the tracking stage, with the final tonal shaping happening at Fascination Street during Bogren's mix.\n\nCompared to the thin, high-tuned crack of the Slaughter of the Soul snare, the Starclassic Bubinga's extra shell depth gives Erlandsson a fuller sound better suited to 2014's denser, more layered guitar production — a clear marker of how both his gear and the album's overall sonic ambition had matured since 1995.",
